JPA repositories will be auto-configured during start of Spring Boot application.

First check if the auto-configuration found your `WeatherRepository`. In the application log you should see:

    Finished Spring Data repository scanning in NNN ms. Found XXX JPA repository interfaces.

The number of repositories XXX should equals the actual number of JPA repositories in your application.

If the number is 0 then check the package of the main application class. For auto-configuration to work smoothly it should be something like:

    package com.example;

because it will be the base package for scanning your application for JPA entities and repositories. The other classes should follow this convention using for example:

    package com.example.jpa;
    package com.example.mvc;

